com.OODPAssn1

Class STARS

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.OODPAssn1.STARS

  • public class STARS
extends java.lang.Object
    The STARS class retrieves information from CourseManagers and UserManagers and handles their data so that CourseManager and UserManager are completely separated and will not have dependencies on each other.
    In short, STARS does the heavy lifting while CourseManager and UserManager should only be concerned with handling their own data.

      • student_EnrolIndex

        public int student_EnrolIndex(int indexNo,
                              java.lang.String matricNo)
        Parameters:
        indexNo - Index Number to enrol into
        matricNo - Matriculation number of the student to enroll
        Returns:
        Error occured - 0
        Added into waitlist - 1
        Successfully enrolled into index - 1
        Already enrolled in index - 2
        Already in waitlist of the index - 3
        Index Clash - 4
        Already in another index of the same course - 5
        Succesfully switched index - 6
        Switched index but added into waitlist of the target index - 7

        Error - 0
        Success - 1
        Success(In waitlist) - 2
        Failed(Already in Index) - 3
        Failed(Already in Index waitlist) - 4
        Failed(Already in another Index of the same course) - 5
        Failed(Already in wait list of another Index of the same course) - 6
        Failed(Clash timing) - 7
